# ============================================================
# ECONOMY CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: economy
scope: economy.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for economy.

## policy_rules
Economy policy constrains:
- what value flows are allowed
- who may see which economic detail
- when cross-domain economic effects are valid
- when economic paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- value-flow allowance must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- cross-domain allowance must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public economic summary
- participant-scoped detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical economic detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow economic action only for valid scope
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden widening of value effect
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If economic context,
value-flow basis,
cross-domain scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the economy path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- value-flow policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
- escalation rules are explicit
